			<h4>Week 28</h4>

			<p><b>Baby : </b>The baby is busy these days blinking - outside in the real world, blinking is necessary to help keep foreign objects out of the eyes. That skill is just one of an already impressive repertoir of tricks she's working on, like coughing, more intense sucking, hiccups and perhaps most important, better breathing.</p>
			<p>Dreaming about your baby at 28 weeks pregnant? Baby may be dreaming about you too. brain  wave activity measured in a developing foetus shows different sleep cycles including the rapid eye movement phase - the stage when dreaming occurs.</p>
			<p>the baby's brain is clearly divided into two hemispheres. it is moon on outside but now it is covered in grooves and ridges . do it is still developing it can already sense the smell,light , sounds and optical inputs. Occasionally the baby opens its eyes and closes it. The baby can already fix its gaze at one point.</p>
			<p>the internal organs are ready to go they start producing enzymes and hormones. The liver starts producing the bile. Baby floates in the amniotic fluid. It swallows  some which is excreted by kidney as urine and the later some of  amniotic fluid will be converted into its first poop.( meconium) blood production is now handled by the bone marrow.</p>
			<p>it has all the elements of red blood cells platelets and white blood cells just like that of an adult.</p>
			<p>The growing foetus sleeps more. Cycles are large its mostly a sleep but most of its sleep is active sleep  which is evident by eye ball rolling, kicks and jerks. it's after 30 weeks of pregnancy when the baby has the phases of sleep just like in a drill that is deep sleep and active sleep.</p>
			<p>If the babies born now with the help of doctors there are chances that it may survive as long as structurally well developed the baby might need surfactant at this point of life if it decides to come early.</p>
			
			<p><b>Mother :</b> welcome to the third trimester, time to actively prepare for labour and motherhood.</p>
			<p>Gone most likely, are the days when you could call pregnancy comfortable that is if you ever did. Now your baby is kicking  keeping you up at night and worried during the day. Your feet are swollen, you are getting tired all over again and your backache is a pain that just won't quit. And even though she hasn't started crying yet. here it may seem like a baby is getting on your nerves already literally as he gets settled into position for birth, her head and your enlarging uterus may rest on the sciatic nerve in the lower part of your enlarging uterus. If that happens you may feel sharp shooting pain, tingling or numbness that starts in your buttocks and radiates down the back of your legs. The pain of sciatica can be quite intense at times and though it may pass if your baby shifts in positions. it can also Linger until you are delivered. A heating pad, a warm tub, stretches or just some self-imposed bed can rest help with the discomfort, so can some complementary and alternative therapies.</p>
			<p>Sensitive skin can surface during pregnancy, even  someone's never had sensitive skin before. Some parts of the body may react because they are dry and flaky, others because of heat rash or an external irritant like the lotion you have been using the past 10 years which is suddenly driving you crazy. the most Sensitive of  it is Belly as it stretches, other potential trouble spots include your hips and thighs.</p>

			<p><b>Tips</b></p>
			<p><b>RH status :</b> Do you know your RH status if not it's important to find out if you are is negative and your baby is RH positive you need a vaccine like injection of RH immune globulin this week to prevent the development of antibodies.</p>
			<p><b>Breast changes :</b> The finding of breast lump can be scary, rest assured it is more than likely nothing to worry about. Having breast cancer during pregnancy is very rare especially if you are under 35.</p>
			<p> The many changes that are happening to your breast while your expecting can cause them to feel much more lumpy, heavy and firm then you are used to.</p>

			<p><b>Fill your iron stores :</b> Baby absorbs the majority of her and stores during the third trimester.</p>
			<p>Vitamin c is iron's best buddy since it can improve iron absorption.</p>

