			<h4>Week 30</h4>
			<p><b>Baby :</b> Until now, its surface was smooth, but now your foetus brain is taking on those characteristic grooves and indentation. The reason for different appearance - those wrinkles allow for an increase amount of brain tissue a necessary change as your baby prepares to develop Street smarts for life outside your womb.The baby's brain is still maturing. All the hemispheres are now trying to co-ordinate the baby's movement. Baby even starts reacting to the stimuli like movements on hearing noises. Baby demonstrates something encountered  unfamiliar. baby reacts to even mothers emotions or if she eat's something tasty or if she has some unfamiliar touch over the belly.</p>
			<p>Nostrils are free of mucus plug now so baby starts practicing breathing in an out which can be appreciated in sonography as the movement of amniotic fluid in an out as well as the haphazardly coordinated movements of lungs and diaphragms. The lungs are not mature to practice breathing at present, haphazard movements of ribs can be visualised on sonography. Sometimes if the baby hiccups it is felt as shop floor in the mother's stomach.</p>
			<p>Your belly's increasing size is a definite clue that your baby is getting bigger everyday.</p>
			<p>Lanugo is disappearing Now that babies brain and new fat cells are regulating her body temperature, the lanugo- that soft downy hair covering your little beans body is beginning to disappear.</p>
			<p>Another big change at 30 weeks pregnant - your baby's bone marrow has completely taken over production of red blood cells. Before tissue groups and then the spleen took care of producing the blood cells. This is an important step for your baby because it means she will be better able to thrive on her own once she is born. Iron is essential element that is transferred from mother to foetus at a higher pace between 28 to 30 weeks of pregnancy. During the entire pregnancy 300 milligram of iron is transferred to foetus so that after the baby is born, he is having good store of iron in the liver and bone marrow so that they can produce their own red blood cells.</p>

			<p><b>Mother :</b> Most of people assume at 30 weeks,  the baby occupies its head down position in uterus which is necessary for smooth delivery, but that's not so true! Because the babies are having unstable lie at this moment as amount of liquor is also more. It's always like they are playing in a swimming pool by 34 to 36 weeks of pregnancy. They will occupy their head down position or else the consultant will suggest you some exercises which can help them get into the head down bottoms up position.</p>
			<p>These days you may feel as though you have got a flamethrower in your chest. Indigestion is one of the most common and annoying pregnancy ailments. </p>
			<p>Here's why: The same pregnancy hormones that causes your body's pelvic muscles to relax so you can deliver your baby also relax the ring of muscle that separates the oesophagus from the stomach. As a result food and digestive juices can head upstream from your tummy into your chest and throat hence your expanding uterus now exerting pressure on your stomach, only fuels the fire.</p>
			<p>So how do you spell relief, avoid food that can cause digestive discomfort like spicy, fatty or fried dishes, chocolate and tomato sauce - eat smaller meals and don't lie down while snacking or right after eating.</p>

			<p><b>Tips</b></p>
			<p><b>State propped up :</b> your baby is pressing against your diaphragm. As your pregnancy progresses, you may start to feel winded even after minimal amounts of physical exertion. Try sleeping in a semi seated position on your left side with pillows popping you up.</p>
			<p><b>Opt for flats! :</b> Put away the heels! your shifting sense of gravity and using joins leave you clutzier than usual.Prevent falls by wearing flats and watch your step.</p>
			<p><b>Remember your kegels.. :</b> it is a pelvic floor strengthening exercise that really work wonders a stronger pelvic floor better supports your uterus bladder and we'll and it can each pregnancy and postpartum symptoms such as hemorrhoids and urinary incontinence they are easy to do no matter where you are!</p>
			<p>To give them a shot,  tense the muscles around your vagina and anus and hold, same as you would if you were trying to stop the flow of urine working up to 10 seconds. Slowly release and repeat, shoot for 3 sets of 20 daily. try doing them during sexual intercourse too.</p>
			<p><b>Fight water retention :</b> though most women associate lots of water with water weight. The opposite is actually true paradoxically, drinking plenty of liquids can keep excessive water retention under control. While a certain amount of pregnancy edema  is to be expected when you're expecting. And represents a normal and necessary increase in body fluids- keeping the fluid flowing can keep too many from accumulating where you would rather didn't like in your ankles.</p>
			<p><b>Check your skin care :</b> Sunscreen with an spf of 30 or higher is your friend now so wear it daily even when there are more clouds than sun.</p>
